@jone I'm not sure UniCurses will help here - I don't think it's a drop-in replacement for the `_curses` module, so unless `blessed` somehow falls back on it it likely won't work.

@marfago what Linux distribution are you using?

It looks like the `*.h` header files for `libncurses` were missing on your system when you built Python, so Python was unable to build the `_curses` module.

On Debian based distributions the development headers should be in a package called `libncurses5-dev`,   on RedHat based distros it should be `ncurses-devel`. After installing those headers you would need to recompile Python unfortunately.

We should probably make any imports of `blessed` conditional, and fall back to a plain boring output if it can't be imported.

